articles.headline: College football recruiting intel: Elite 11 Finals and June's final official visit weekend
articles.description: What we're hearing about one of the most important weekends on the recruiting calendar.

images.name: Landon Duckworth [608x342]
images.caption: Landon Duckworth is one of the top remaining undecided quarterbacks in the Class of 2026.

images.name: Lincoln Riley [608x342]
images.caption: Lincoln Riley's Trojans have the country's deepest recruiting class.

articles.headline: CFP leaders say 'everything's on the table' after meetings wrap
articles.description: CFP executive director Rich Clark said "pretty much everything's on the table" for potential formats for 2026 and beyond but that the group would like to make a decision by the fall.

images.name: Heather Dinich breaks down likelihood of 5+11 CFP format
images.caption: Heather Dinich joins Paul Finebaum to discuss conferences debating whether five automatic bids and 11 at-large ones for 16-team playoff is the future of CFP.

articles.headline: OT Ekene Ogboko, No. 50 in class of '26, commits to Georgia
articles.description: Four-star offensive tackle prospect Ekene Ogboko, No. 50 in the 2026 ESPN 300, has committed to Georgia over Clemson, Florida and Notre Dame, he told ESPN on Wednesday.

images.name: Georgia Bulldogs [600x400]
images.caption: Five-star DT Elijah Griffin has committed to Georgia, turning down Miami and USC.

articles.headline: College football's 10 most unbreakable records
articles.description: A look at the marks that have stood the test of time -- and most likely always will.

images.name: Unbreakable college football records [608x342]
images.caption: Antonio Perkins, Bobby Bowden, Barry Sanders and Nick Saban
images.alt: Antonio Perkins, Bobby Bowden, Barry Sanders and Nick Saban

images.name: Bud Wilkinson [608x342] - Copy (2)
images.caption: Oklahoma's 1956 Orange Bowl victory was part of a 47-game winning streak for coach Bud Wilkinson and the Sooners.

images.name: Barry Sanders [2999x1986]
images.caption: Barry Sanders averaged 238.9 rushing yards for Oklahoma State in 1988.

images.name: Bobby Bowden [3499x2445]
images.caption: Bobby Bowden and Florida State finished in the top 5 of the final AP poll for an amazing 14 consecutive seasons (1987-2000).

images.name: Antonio Perkins [3005x2170]
images.caption: Oklahoma's Antonio Perkins had three punt return touchdowns and 277 punt return yards against UCLA in 2003.

images.name: Oklahoma vs. Texas Tech - (Patrick Mahoms) [608x342] - Copy
images.caption: At Texas Tech, Patrick Mahomes accounted for 819 total yards in a memorable shootout with Baker Mayfield and Oklahoma.

images.name: Nick Saban [3724x3015]
images.caption: In addition to winning six national titles at Alabama, Nick Saban's Tide had 100 consecutive wins over unranked opponents.

articles.headline: Eyeing NFL, three-star QB Jett Thomalla commits to Alabama
articles.description: Coach Kalen DeBoer and Alabama completed a flip of three-star Iowa State quarterback pledge Jett Thomalla, a record-setting signal-caller from Omaha, Nebraska, finishing the Crimson Tide's efforts to land a passer in the 2026 class this spring.

images.name: Kalen DeBoer announces Alabama's starting QB and discusses new additions
images.caption: DeBoer declares Ty Simpson as the Crimson Tide's starting quarterback for the upcoming season and expresses his confidence in their ability to win big games.

articles.headline: Illinois' Bielema wants 9 league games for all conferences
articles.description: Speaking Tuesday before Illini Night at Wrigley Field, Illinois coach Bret Bielema told reporters he'd like to see the College Football Playoff expand to 16 teams in 2026, but only if all the major conferences, including the SEC, play nine league games.

images.name: Greg Sankey discusses future of SEC amid NCAA changes
images.caption: SEC Commissioner Sankey shares insights on the NCAA settlement, including scholarship increases, revenue shifts and how it all impacts the future of college sports.
